D. Acquisition Strategy
The acquisition strategy permits accelerated fielding of laser weapon systems in the Fleet and provides a demand signal for the industrial base to expand the capacity
to develop and manufacture this advanced technology. The acquisition strategy of this Non-Program of Record (POR) consists of the use of existing contracts and key
warfare centers, FFRDCs, and national Test Ranges to conduct the Directed Energy Testing Against Missiles (DETAM) effort. DETAM will allow for industry-developed
technology insertions to be integrated with government Directed Energy (DE) capabilities in short timeframes to modernize High Energy Laser (HEL) technology.
The acquisition structure will address the National Defense Strategy and foster a culture of affordability in HEL system testing, evaluation, and advanced component

