Research Instrumentation Prgm

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Defense University Research Instrumentation Program (DURIP) funds are awarded to universities to purchase high- cost research instrumentation that is normally
not provided for in single-investigator research grants. Individual grants may range from $50K to $3.0M. Proposals for DURIP awards are submitted to the Services
(Army, Navy, Air Force, Space Force) in response to a public Funding Opportunity Announcement (FOA). Proposals received by the Office of Naval Research (ONR)
are reviewed and all valid proposals received are prioritized. The Office of the Secretary of War (OSW) reviews, selects and announces all Department of War (DoW)
awardees. Universities awarded grants are required to purchase the instrumentation and take delivery before any billing occurs. DURIP awards provide one-year
funding. The DURIP proposal and award cycle is required to be completed within one fiscal year.

