The FY 2026 request for Large Unmanned Surface Vessels (LUSV) includes $0 of discretionary funding and
$57,860 thousands of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $57,860 thousand.

In FY26, USV support will focus on the prototyping phase of USVs and the testing and verification of prototypes
and design reviews, culminating with determining success criteria in order to award follow on production OTAs.
This work also entails finalizing Contract Data Requirements List (CDRL) requirements, J-Attachments, and
Statement of Work, ensuring requirements are properly mapped to LUSV documentation and the solicitation is
executable. Industry feedback is vital to this phase, and so inputs and clarification questions will be taken and
implemented as part of the draft RFP release to industry. Documentation drafting and finalization, to include
but not limited to, logistics documentation, technical documentation, and contract documentation to support the
prototyping and follow-on production phase.

Prototype operations support will focus on maintaining the prototypes, ensuring spares and maintenance
is properly scheduled and conducted. A proper logistics tail and footprint is vital to successfully operating
these prototypes and allows lessons learned to be documented and implemented into USV requirements
documentation, ensuring maturation of USVs.
