Remarks
Funding for PE 0603564N and PE 0603573N is directly interrelated, as the ship design activities in PU 0603564N/0411 (DDG(X) Concept Development) provide the
initial specifications that drive requirements for the Integrated Power System (IPS) and major component procurements in PU 0603573N/2471. In FY27, these efforts
will transition to support the BBG(X) platform. The DDG(X) concept development work within PE 0603564N/PU 0411 will shift to BBG(X) efforts in PU 0413, while the
corresponding DDG(X) Power & Propulsion Risk Mitigation & Demonstration funding within PE 0603573N PU 2471 will be reprogrammed to the new PU 2486 (BBG(X)
IPS) to align with the next-generation platform.

D. Acquisition Strategy
A formal acquisition strategy for DDG(X) is still being developed and will align with Section 130 of the FY 2023 NDAA (CONTRACTS FOR DESIGN AND
CONSTRUCTION OF THE DDG(X) DESTROYER PROGRAM). Preliminary, Contract, and Detail Designs for DDG(X) will be accomplished through a collaborative,
multidisciplinary Navy/Industry team composed of the LSC shipbuilders, suppliers, ship design agents and other subject matter experts. The Navy's intent is to ensure a
smooth, overlapping transition between Arleigh Burke (DDG-51) Class and DDG(X). As maturity of the design increases, it is expected that the shipbuilders will take on
an increasing level of responsibility for the design.

 DDG(X) program is transitioning to BBG(X) as addressed in PU 0413 with new BBG(X) contract awards.




