A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Budget provides funding for multiple lines of improvement across the Navy's portfolio of reusable and expendable undersea warfare targets.

1. Provides funding for a Long Endurance Variant of MK 39 Mod 4 Expendable Mobile ASW Training Target (EMATT) to support 24+ hour missions. This effort supports
development of Long Endurance module for the MK 39 Mod 4 EMATT. The Long Endurance module will allow the EMATT to support training of multiple aircrews in a
single, coordinated extended tracking exercise and facilitate the training of multiple watch sections on surface ships and submarines in an extended tracking exercise.

2. Provides funding for an Extremely Low Frequency Variant of MK 39 MOD 4 Expendable Mobile ASW Training Target (EMATT) to support narrowband tracking
requirements for USN submarines. This effort supports the development of a Low Frequency module for the MK 39 MOD 4 EMATT. The Low Frequency Variant
upgrade allows EMATT to better emulate low frequency signatures of modern threat submarines.

3. Provides funding to initiate development efforts starting in FY 2027 to add Magnetic Anomaly Detection (MAD) wire to allow stimulation of MH-60R capability to MK39
MOD 4 EMATT.

