A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Fleet Experimentation (FLEX) program examines materiel and non-materiel initiatives in development to address the fleet's most critical warfighting priorities
and gaps. Commander, U.S. Naval Forces Europe/Africa, Commander, U.S. Pacific Fleet, and Commander, U.S. Fleet Forces Command (CUSFFC) are the FLEX
Program Owners. Per the current FLEX Instruction (3900.1E), they provide program oversight, Commanders' FLEX guidance with experimentation priorities, funding
oversight, and advocacy for the most viable recommended solutions to fleet priority capability gaps. CUSFFC manages FLEX program funding. Director, Navy Warfare
Development Center (NWDC) serves as the Executive Agent (EA) and is responsible for FLEX campaign design and management, experiment planning and execution,
analysis, final reporting, and post-experiment actions. FLEX results drive action across three structured return on investment (ROI) categories: capability development,
investment, and delivery.

